"'''Do or Do Not'''" is a comic appearing in [[Star Wars Tales 15|''Star Wars Tales'' 15]] and collected in ''[[Star Wars Tales Volume 4]]'' and ''[[Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The New Republic Vol. 1]]''.

==Plot summary==
Several days after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] is on [[Endor/Legends|Endor]], questioning why [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] have not reappeared to [[Gender/Legends|him]]. [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]] and [[Han Solo/Legends|Han]] walk by and overhear him yelling into thin air, and Leia decides to speak with him.

Luke confesses that he is unsure of his place anymore&mdash;having learned in a short space of [[Time/Legends|time]] that he is the last [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] and that Leia is his sister&mdash;or how the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] will rebuild [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], before saying that he's lonely. Leia comforts him that he'll always have his friends and family, and Luke agrees. Jokingly, he suggests that someday she and Han will have Jedi [[Youngling/Legends|children]] for him to [[Jedi training/Legends|train]]. When Leia answers with a skeptical "maybe," the [[Force ghost/Legends|ghost]] of Yoda appears and gives Luke a wink.

